# AB Implement

Start from the approved plan. Do not re-plan unless it is missing, stale, unsafe, or materially ambiguous. When the user says "go ahead", implement.

Own the landing lane. Recover repo, branch/worktree, PR/Linear/plan state, local dev needs, and whether commits, pushes, PRs, merges, or cleanup were requested. Use a new branch unless asked to work directly in main.

Implement simply: durable domain behavior, thin adapters, singular sources of truth, explicit side effects, deleted dead code, and small behavior-owned modules. Avoid speculative abstractions and pre-alpha compatibility scaffolding unless required.

After the first working pass, simplify with code-reaper principles: remove dead code, collapse unnecessary abstractions, tighten ownership, and make the diff easier to review.

Definition of local testing: Actually physically testing the application and the features that we implemented using the dev server and browser use, 200's on api calls are not good enough and only just the start of dev testing. 

