Overlap slow gates once stable: autoreview, PR CI, bot review, and manual QA all in parallel if possible. Use autoreview `--parallel-tests` when useful. If code changes, stale reviews can be rerun.

Handle feedback with judgment: verify findings, fix in-scope defects, reject weak/speculative ones briefly, and escalate scope-breaking findings.

If asked to merge, merge only after relevant proof, CI, and review surfaces have settled. Pull/update main and clean temporary state within scope.

